text: Teclla (possibly from Quechua for eyelash; two-colored, or for 'with alternating colors') is a mountain in the Chila mountain range in the Andes of Peru. It is located in the Arequipa Region, Caylloma Province, Lari District. Teclla lies northwest of Mismi and Quehuisha. ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Arequipa Region
title: Teclla (mountain)
